NAME
	invert_exit - returns an opposing exit

SYNOPSIS
	string invert_exit(string exit)

DESCRIPTION
	Returns an exit opposite of the exit arg, or "unknown" if exit
	arg does not have an opposite.

RETURN VALUE
	Returns a string representing the opposite direction of the input.
	Up returns "down", east returns "west".  If the opposite is unknown
	return "unknown".

EXAMPLES
	string x;

	x = invert_exit("up");
	x = invert_exit("northwest");

SEE ALSO
	safun/article
